Popular Blog SB Nation Furloughs Writers With Few Sports to Cover During PandemicEnlarge this image toggle caption Nam Y. Huh/AP Nam Y. Huh/APWith few to no sporting events taking place because of the coronavirus crisis, sports journalism is feeling the crunch.
Several of those furloughs are hitting the media group's flagship sports website SB Nation.
Vox Media also owns websites The Verge, Vox, Eater, Polygon and Curbed, in addition to SB Nation.
Bankoff indicated in the email that editorial furloughs would only take place at SB Nation and Curbed.
Plenty of furloughed staff members at SB Nation praised one another's work in the wake of the company's move.